PN,30401
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FIt was the loudest and longest
OL,7,Fapplause of Andy Burmham's 30-minute
OL,8,Fspeech: a pledge to oversee the
OL,9,Fbiggest council house building
OL,10,Fprogramme since the post-war.
OL,12,FFor if you could boil down
OL,13,F"Burnhamism" to a single policy issue,
OL,14,Fit would be housing.
OL,16,F"If you don't give people a good home,
OL,17,Fwhat chance do they have of having a
OL,18,Fgood life?," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,F"Everything starts with a good home,
OL,7,Fand this country finally has to put
OL,8,Fthat at the top of its priority list."
OL,10,FAll roads lead back to housing for
OL,11,FBritain's next prime minister ` the
OL,12,Fstate of the NHS, children's education
OL,13,Fprospects, inequality, the welfare
OL,14,Fbill, economic growth.
OL,16,FNo would-be PM in modern times has
OL,17,Fgiven it this much prominence.
OL,19,FSo, to his solution then: more council
OL,20,Fhousing and lots of it. Before we deal
OL,21,Fwith the how, lets deal with the why.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FWhy council housing?
OL,8,FA very brief history: in the post-war
OL,9,Fera that Burnham refers to, Britain
OL,10,Fbuilt around 5 million council homes.
OL,12,FNot just Labour, but Conservative
OL,13,Fgovernments too (in fact it was under
OL,14,Fthe Tories in the 1950s that the
OL,15,Fhighest annual number of council homes
OL,16,Fwas ever built).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FThere was a political consensus,
OL,7,Fbetween 1945 and 1979, that the state
OL,8,Fshould play a central role in building
OL,9,Faffordable rental homes for its
OL,10,Fcitizens who couldn't afford to buy
OL,11,Fone.
OL,13,FBy 1979, around a third of Britain
OL,14,Flived in a council home. Only around
OL,15,F10% rented privately.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FBut 1979 was when that political
OL,7,Fconsensus died. Margaret Thatcher
OL,8,Fintroduced housing policies that put
OL,9,Fthose numbers in reverse - including
OL,10,Fthe right to buy your council home at
OL,11,Fa generous discount, and the
OL,12,Fderegulation of the private rental
OL,13,Fmarket to boost the number of private
OL,14,Flandlords.
OL,16,FFast forward to 2026, and around 6% of
OL,17,Fpeople live in council housing and 20%
OL,18,Flive in private rental accommodation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FFor the last 45 years, there has been
OL,7,Fa new political consensus: that the
OL,8,Fgovernment should not build homes
OL,9,F(through local councils) and the
OL,10,Fmarket (through private landlords)
OL,11,Fshould instead fill the gap left
OL,12,Fbehind by the millions that were sold
OL,13,Funder Thatcher and never replaced.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FAndy Burnham wants to reverse that
OL,7,Fagain, because homelessness has been
OL,8,Frising, the number of homeless
OL,9,Fchildren living in temporary
OL,10,Faccommodation in families that cannot
OL,11,Fafford to buy or rent a home is the
OL,12,Fhighest on record. Also, and are 1.3
OL,13,Fmillion households on a waiting list
OL,14,Ffor a social housing, because a
OL,15,Fchronic shortage of affordable homes
OL,16,Fmeans only the very neediest are
OL,17,Feligible for social housing.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FThe quality of the remaining housing
OL,7,Fstock that wasn't sold off under Right
OL,8,Fto Buy and is still in use is all too
OL,9,Foften poor, at times squalid and
OL,10,Fsometimes dangerous, as I have been
OL,11,Freporting on for the past five years.
OL,12,FAs we reported back in 2021, the cost
OL,13,Fto the NHS of poor housing is #1.4
OL,14,Fbillion every year.
OL,16,FIn 2023 I reported from a primary
OL,17,Fschool where over half the children
OL,18,Fare homeless, living in hostels and
OL,19,Fbed and breakfasts hours away.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FI have met families being sent to live
OL,7,F200 miles away from everything they
OL,8,Fknow because their local council
OL,9,Fsimply doesn't have any homes for them.
OL,11,FAnd this housing crisis, created by a
OL,12,Flack of housing stock, is still
OL,13,Fcosting taxpayers eye-watering amounts
OL,14,Fof money. The annual housing benefit
OL,15,Fbill ` which is paid out by the
OL,16,Fgovernment to renters to help them top
OL,17,Fup their rent ` is #38 billion. That
OL,18,Fis over half the UK defence budget.
OL,19,FThat is because rents are increasingly
OL,20,Funaffordable even for working people.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FRather than spend money on bricks, the
OL,7,FBritish government spends billions on
OL,8,Fbenefits, a good chunk of which goes
OL,9,Fto private landlords, some of whom
OL,10,Fbought or inherited the house they now
OL,11,Frent out thanks to Right to Buy from a
OL,12,Flocal council.
OL,14,FAndy Burnham has concluded that the
OL,15,Fonly way to solve all those problems
OL,16,Fis to build council houses again, not
OL,17,Fto leave those families to the market,
OL,18,Fwhich has failed to fill the gap left
OL,19,Fbehind when successive governments
OL,20,Fretreated from housebuilding.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FAnd he's talking about council
OL,7,Fhousing, not social housing. That
OL,8,Fcould be a very significant
OL,9,Fdistinction.
OL,11,FSocial housing refers to housing
OL,12,Fprovided either by local councils or
OL,13,Fnot-for-profit housing associations at
OL,14,Faround 50% of local market rent.
OL,16,FIn the post-war era, council was king
OL,17,Fand dominated social housing. In 1979
OL,18,F93% of social housing was council, 7%
OL,19,Fwas housing associations (which were
OL,20,Ftypically small, hyperlocal charitable
OL,21,Forganisations).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FToday however, the majority of social
OL,7,Fhousing is housing association-owned,
OL,8,Faccounting for 61%, and housing
OL,9,Fassociations have changed dramatically
OL,10,F` no longer just small, local
OL,11,Fproviders but dominated by enormous,
OL,12,Fcorporate entities with more than
OL,13,F100,000 homes, revenues of up to #1
OL,14,Fbillion and CEOs on #400,000 plus a
OL,15,Fyear.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30413
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FFrom the 1980s, as councils were
OL,7,Fstarved of government cash and blocked
OL,8,Ffrom borrowing to replace the homes
OL,9,Fthey sold, housing associations became
OL,10,Fthe preferred choice of Conservative
OL,11,Fand Labour governments.
OL,13,FHousing associations were granted
OL,14,Fpermission to access private finance
OL,15,Fto build new homes and councils were
OL,16,Fencouraged to offload the stock they
OL,17,Fhad built and managed since the war
OL,18,Fand give it to housing associations as
OL,19,Fpart of 'Large-Scale Voluntary
OL,20,FTransfer agreements'.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30414
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FThe idea was to get the national
OL,7,Fhousing spend off the Treasury's
OL,8,Fbalance sheet, and get specialised
OL,9,Fproviders to look after social housing
OL,10,Finstead to drive up standards.
OL,12,FBut as I have found in my
OL,13,Finvestigation into social housing,
OL,14,Fhousing associations don't always
OL,15,Fequal better housing. Far from it - we
OL,16,Fdiscovered squalid, dangerous homes
OL,17,Frun by the biggest providers in social
OL,18,Fhousing, where money could not be an
OL,19,Fexcuse.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30415
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FAgain, it looks as though Andy Burnham
OL,7,Fwants to reverse this trend, with
OL,8,Fpower and resource going back to local
OL,9,Fcouncils. That would be a significant
OL,10,Fshift in social housing.
OL,12,FWhich leads us to the next obvious
OL,13,Fquestion ` how?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30416
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FThe question is not just how can a
OL,7,FBurnham administration pay for the
OL,8,Fbiggest council house building
OL,9,Fprogramme in decades, but how can
OL,10,Fcouncils build on such a large scale
OL,11,Fwithout the corporate memory of doing
OL,12,Fso, with the cost of materials and a
OL,13,Fnational skill and labour shortage?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30417
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FThe Starmer government's promise to
OL,7,Fbuild 1.5 million homes by 2029
OL,8,Falready requires an estimated 240,000
OL,9,Fmore construction workers. The
OL,10,Fgovernment has started to address this
OL,11,Fwith more funding for training but
OL,12,Fwould need to accelerate enormously to
OL,13,Fmeet the new PM's ambitions.
OL,15,FThe overall cost though of such a
OL,16,Fprogramme will be the ultimate
OL,17,Fchallenge for Andy Burnham, who has
OL,18,Fpromised to stick to the fiscal rules
OL,19,Fof living within the country's means.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30418
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FState-funded housebuilding on the
OL,7,Fscale seen after 1945 can only be done
OL,8,Fwith extra borrowing, so Burnham will
OL,9,Fhave to find a way of bending rather
OL,10,Fthan breaking those rules, borrowing
OL,11,Fto invest.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30419
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FHe will likely move to convince the
OL,7,Fbond markets that such spending is not
OL,8,Fonly sensible but necessary to bring
OL,9,Fdown the UK's welfare spending on
OL,10,Fhousing, that the only way you reduce
OL,11,Fthat #38 billion housing benefit bill
OL,12,Fis building affordable homes that mean
OL,13,Ffewer people need help with their
OL,14,Frent, with the State providing long
OL,15,Fterm housing support with safe, decent
OL,16,Fhomes that don't make people sick and
OL,17,Fallow children to succeed in education.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30420
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FThere is some research out there on
OL,7,Fthis. Shelter and the National Housing
OL,8,FFederation, working with the Centre
OL,9,Ffor Economics and Business Research,
OL,10,Fconclude that it would cost the state
OL,11,F#35.4 billion to build 90,000 social
OL,12,Fhomes per year (that's the number
OL,13,Fexperts say is needed to meet current
OL,14,Fdemand).
OL,16,FIt is an eye-watering up-front cost,
OL,17,Fbut the report finds a large-scale
OL,18,Fsocial house building programme would
OL,19,Fbreak even in three years, from which
OL,20,Fpoint the economic benefits would
OL,21,Foutweigh the costs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30421
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FA substantial economic boost to the
OL,7,Fconstruction industry, a reduction in
OL,8,Fthe housing benefit bill and "wider
OL,9,Findirect benefits including reduced
OL,10,Fhomelessness, increased employment and
OL,11,Fsavings on healthcare" mean the
OL,12,Fcountry would not only save money but
OL,13,Fit would begin to generate #2.4
OL,14,Fbillion a year.
OL,16,FThat is the argument Burnham will have
OL,17,Fto make. It is an argument no British
OL,18,FPrime Minister has attempted for
OL,19,Fnearly 50 years.
OL,26,@pD@^OUsD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30422
SC,0022
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782762495
OL,3,CWhat could "Burnhamism" mean for
OL,4,Chousing?
OL,6,FFor decades successive governments
OL,7,Fhave treated housing like a secondary
OL,8,Fissue. That looks all set to change,
OL,9,Fif Andy Burmham sticks to his promises
OL,10,Fto but housing at the centre of his
OL,11,Fpolitical project.
